set('profile_content', <<<HTML
	<p>Linda Lim is Professor of Strategy at the Stephen M. Ross School of Business at the University of Michigan. She earned a PhD in economics from Michigan and a Masters from Yale University. Her current research is on Singapore’s economy; on foreign direct investment by Chinese companies in Southeast Asia; and on local entrepreneurs in Southeast Asia. At Michigan, she has served as Director Center for Southeast Asian Studies, on executive committee for Center for International Business Education and Research, the Center for Chinese Studies, and as Associate Director of the International Institute.</p>
	<p>Linda has advised international institutions including, but not limited to, the U.S. State Department and the U.S. Trade Representatives, the U.S. Congress’ House Subcommittee on Asia and the Pacific, and the United Nations General Assembly Economic Committee. She was an independent director at NASDAQ traded Woodhead Industries and is currently an independent member of the board of publically-traded Multi-Fineline Electronix.  Linda is a Trustee Emeritus of The Asia Society.</p>
